Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Keep covered off heat until ready to mash in step 5.

While potatoes cook, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @brown sugar bourbon seasoning{10.8%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. 

> TIP: If the steak begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer steak to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork; cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

While steak cooks, cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until lightly browned, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and dice @apple{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add apple and scallion whites; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ½ cup water, and @sugar{½%tsp}. Cook until sauce has thickened and apple is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

In the last 2 minutes, return steak to pan until warmed through. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

> Use pan used for chicken or steak here.

Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth.

Stir in scallion greens, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @butter{1%tbsp}, and a splash of reserved potato cooking liquid. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If needed, add more potato cooking liquid a splash at a time until potatoes are smooth and creamy.

Divide steak, mashed potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Top steak with apple pan sauce and serve.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.